Headlines.Author: John Kell
Headlines.Headline: QEP Resources 3Q Output Grew 41%; Boosts 2010 Forecast Again

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES QEP Resources Inc. QEP again boosted its 2010 output forecast as it reported a 41% increase in the third quarter from a year earlier. The oil-and-gas producer said results were led by "strong" performances at its Haynesville, Woodford 'Cana' and Granite Wash plays. President and Chief Executive Chuck Stanley said the company's focus on efficiency is resulting in "industry-leading completed well costs in our core resource plays." As such, QEP is now projecting 2010 output to range from 225 billion to 227 billion cubic feet of oil equivalent, up from the July view of 218 billion to 222 billion.

Headlines.Author: Michael Aneiro
Headlines.Headline: Summer of Junk: High-Yield Bond Issuance Is On Record-Setting Pace

PARAGRAPH.#text: (Updates issuance data in second paragraph; adds investor commentary.) NEW YORK (Dow Jones)--Junk-bond issuance is on a record-setting pace this week, with a flurry of new offerings in the market Wednesday adding to the uncommonly high total seen this August. This week has already produced $7.9 billion in high-yield bond issuance, the highest single-week total since late April, according to data provider Dealogic, and on pace to surpass the $12.5 billion one-week record set in December 2006. U.S. high-yield volume has reached a record high year-to-date volume of $148 billion, up 77% from the $83.6 billion at this point in 2009 and just $15.6 billion short of the $163.6 billion full-year 2009 total.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Summer of Junk: High-Yield Bond Issuance Is On Record-Setting Pace
